The transaction price of TP/SL cannot be guaranteed. It depends entirely on the market at the time. For large positions, please stop profit and stop loss in batches to avoid large slippage!

Although price limit stop loss can limit price slippage, it cannot guarantee a certain transaction! When setting the order price, try to keep a reasonable distance between the trigger price and the trigger price to make the limit order easier to be traded!

In order to prevent the market price transaction pin from triggering the stop loss and causing accidental injury, we have introduced a smoother marked price as the target. When the latest price deviates from the marked price too much, the stop loss will not be triggered!

Realized profit and loss is the profit and loss after all positions are closed, including fees, funding, and profit and loss on closing position.
Settled profit and loss is the income that has been settled to the user\'s balance, including transaction fees, capital costs, liquidation profit and loss, settlement income, etc.

1. When you trade in the contract market, if the market declines, your position margin will be insufficient. Please keep in mind that the exchange Swap will place a mandatory liquidation order and send you liquidation details according to the system agreement. 
2. Please read carefully and follow the business rules of the exchange Swap. Understand the contract mechanism and operation principle, understand the various risks of the market, and reasonably arrange funds for trading. 
3. Under certain extreme market conditions, it may be difficult or impossible to close out your open positions. For example, when your profit ranks first in the effective contract PnL in the entire contract market, and the insurance fund is insufficient to cover the losses. 
4. In case of changes in local laws, regulations and policies, amendments to bourse trading rules, and introduction of emergency measures, the exchange will notice you in advance that you may not maintain open positions, but the position margin and profitable balance will still be paid! 
5. For any reasons beyond the control of the exchange, such as earthquakes, floods, fire and other factors or computer system and communication system failures, etc., your order may not be executed in part or in whole, and you may suffer losses therefrom. 
6. Like speculative transactions,"hedging" transactions also face the risks caused by price fluctuations. Please understand the relevant mechanism in advance. 
7. If you lend your account to a third party, the safety of your contract deposit may be affected. Please carefully protect your personal account.
